41, "tags": [], "time": "2005-05-24T17:32:05Z", "text": "Open the attachment in IE and the same attachment in Firefox.\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/attachment.cgi?id=184404\nThen, in IE, in the file found above, select the longest item in the select box.\n You will see that the text field is dynamically resized per the javascript in\nthe html file and then is populated with the untruncated value from the select\nbox.  Now, if you perform the same exact steps in the same exact file in\nFirefox.  The text field is dynamically resized but the value is truncated. \nFirefox continues to treat the text field as having a size 30 even though it has\nbeen resized.", "id": 2510335, "raw_text": "Open the attachment in IE and the same attachment in Firefox.\nhttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/attachment.cgi?id=184404\nThen, in IE, in the file found above, select the longest item in the select box.\n You will see that the text field is dynamically resized per the javascript in\nthe html file and then is populated with the untruncated value from the select\nbox.  Now, if you perform the same exact steps in the same exact file in\nFirefox.  The text field is dynamically resized but the value is truncated. \nFirefox continues to treat the text field as having a size 30 even though it has\nbeen resized.", "creator": "robert@solsticeinc.net"}, {"tags": [], "time": "2005-05-25T00:24:12Z", "id": 2510726, "text": "JavaScript is case-sensitive.  If your script were changed to read\n\"Query.pv_notify.maxLength\" (note the capital L), it would work as expected.\n\nIf you have no further complaints then this bug can be resolved as INVALID as it\nis not a bug with the browser.", "bug_id": 295341, "creator": "djpohly+bmo@gmail.com", "attachment_id": null, "count": 4, "author": "djpohly+bmo@gmail.com", "creation_time": "2005-05-25T00:24:12Z", "is_private": false, "raw_text": "JavaScript is case-sensitive.  If your script were changed to read\n\"Query.pv_notify.maxLength\" (note the capital L), it would work as expected.\n\nIf you have no further complaints then this bug can be resolved as INVALID as it\nis not a bug with the browser."}, {"bug_id": 295341, "id": 2511182, "text": "Well what do you know?, it does work with a capital L, and I thought the problem\nwas with the size attribute, but the size attribute was working the whole time,\nbut the maxLength was less than the size value.  Thanks for the rapid help.", "time": "2005-05-25T14:19:53Z", "tags": [], "raw_text": "Well what do you know?, it does work with a capital L, and I thought the problem\nwas with the size attribute, but the size attribute was working the whole time,\nbut the maxLength was less than the size value.  Thanks for the rapid help.", "is_private": false, "creation_time": "2005-05-25T14:19:53Z", "author": "robert@solsticeinc.net", "count": 5, "attachment_id": null, "creator": "robert@solsticeinc.net"}]}}, "comments": {}}